Police in Alldays outside Makhado have opened a case of culpable homicide after the death of a mine worker at the Venetia Mine. 31-year-old Maggie Dimakatso Semata was crushed to death when she allegedly fell onto a conveyor belt at the Mine. The conveyor belt ultimately dragged her into a stone scrubber where her body was found trapped between the rocks with multiple wounds. Investigations are continuing. -TNA Reporter   